It looks like my response got cut off!

No worries, I'll just continue from where we left off.

So, tell me more about your beach trip and the amazing shots you got! What was it about the sunset that inspired you to capture it? Was there a particular moment or scene that stood out to you?

And how did you find the experience of shooting with a camera again after a break? Did you feel like you got back into the swing of things quickly, or was it a bit of a learning curve to get used to a new camera and settings?

I'm all ears (or in this case, all text) and would love to hear more about your photography adventure!
